article.headline: Georgia Southern 96, Reinhardt 61
article.story: Statesboro, Ga. -- Georgia Southern beat Reinhardt 96-61, extending their home-opening win streak to 28 games. The Eagles were led by Antonio Hanson, who scored 19 points on 7-for-9 shooting. GSU also extended their non-conference home winning streak to 25, a run that dates back to 2002. Tyler Troupe contributed 15 points and 12 rebounds for the Eagles (2-1). Georgia Southern shot 65.4% (17-for-26) from the floor in the first half and 59.3% (35-for-59) for the game. The Eagles had four players score in double figures. Mario Mason scored 14 points to lead Reinhardt (1-2). Reinhardt trailed 20-18 with 11:36 to play in the first half, but GSU scored the next five points and reeled off a 12-2 run. The Eagles finished the half on a 12-2 spurt to lead 44-26 at the break.
